A few of the things that help me are continuity notes. I consider them after-the-fact outlines, and have found I can leave a piece sitting for months and reabsorb what I need to know in minutes

I can remember my story just fine, but because of my glacial writing pace, I've found myself increaslingly reliant on catchup moments for the readers since i'm not exactly a writer of note, so expecting people to keep track of my meanderings isn't exactly ideal.
